			<div class="comment-meta"><span class="comment-author vcard"><cite class="fn" title="http://tammyandteddys.com"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130702043700/http://tammyandteddys.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-commentauthor','https://web.archive.org/web/20130702043700/http://tammyandteddys.com']);" title="Carol Skowronek" class="url" rel="external nofollow">Carol Skowronek</a></cite></span><!-- .comment-author .vcard --> <span class="published"><abbr class="comment-date" title="Saturday, June 29th, 2013, 5:56 am">June 29, 2013</abbr> at <abbr class="comment-time" title="Saturday, June 29th, 2013, 5:56 am">5:56 am</abbr></span> | <a class="permalink" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130702043700/http://novelideareviews.com/author-interview-giveaway-lindsay-buroker/#comment-957" title="Permalink to comment 957">Permalink</a>  | <a class="comment-reply-link" href="/web/20130702043700/http://novelideareviews.com/author-interview-giveaway-lindsay-buroker/?replytocom=957#respond" onclick="return addComment.moveForm(&quot;comment-957&quot;, &quot;957&quot;, &quot;respond&quot;, &quot;2261&quot;)">Reply</a></div>
			<div class="comment-content comment-text">
				
				<p>Waiting for EE7, I am now read Ann McCaffrey, these a classic books, fast paced adventure.  Her world is made up of dragons and the people that love them and they fight a thing called Thread that comes from another world that destroys all.  Lindsay&#8217;s quality equals Ann McCaffrey and worth the read.  i am not sure how many books but their are more than 20.  Her beloved characters reapear in most books as memory because the time between each books seems to be around 400 years.  If you pick up any of the books it stands alone which the exception of a couple of trilogies which are also great.  I  have not read a Ann McCaffrey book that is boring.  As is expected of Lindsay&#8217;s great adventerous mind, she has only just begun.  Thank you again Lindsay for your great works.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content .comment-text -->

			
		</div><!-- .comment-wrap -->

		
